@startuml
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontSize 16
left to right direction

skinparam rectangle {
  FontSize 16
  FontColor #FFFFFF
  BorderThickness 2
  BorderColor #004578
  RoundCorner 8
}

skinparam arrow {
  Color #FF5C39
  FontSize 15
  FontColor #000000
  Thickness 2
}

skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFF4E5
  FontColor #000000
  BorderColor #FF5C39
  FontSize 15
}

skinparam legend {
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  BorderColor #CCCCCC
  FontSize 15
}

legend top right
  |= Color |= Meaning |
  |<#0078D4>   | Starting state (Standard security) |
  |<#FF5C39>   | Upgrade actions required |
  |<#107C10>   | Protected end state (Trusted Launch) |
end legend

rectangle "**Standard Security VM**\n\nGeneration: Gen2\n\n[ ] Secure Boot: Disabled\n[ ] vTPM: Disabled\n[ ] Integrity monitoring: Disabled\n\nBoot chain: Unverified\nDefender for Cloud: No boot alerts" as Standard #0078D4

rectangle "**Enable Trusted Launch**\n\nDeallocate VM\nChange security type\nEnable components\nRestart" as Steps #FF5C39

rectangle "**Trusted Launch VM**\n\nGeneration: Gen2\n\n[x] Secure Boot: Enforcing signatures\n[x] vTPM: Measuring boot chain\n[x] Integrity monitoring: Active\n\nBoot chain: Cryptographically verified\nDefender for Cloud: Boot alerts enabled" as Trusted #107C10

Standard --> Steps : upgrade\nrequired
Steps --> Trusted : Trusted Launch\nenabled on restart

note bottom of Standard
  New Gen2 VMs default to Trusted Launch
  automatically — no upgrade required.
end note

note bottom of Trusted
  Integrity monitoring requires
  explicit enablement on all paths.
end note

@enduml
